Business Brief -- BJ Services Co.:
   Oil Field Company to Close
   Its Operations in Canada
In a statement, BJ Services said "the one-time charge to
earnings shall be recouped in less than one year through the
elimination of operating losses in Canada" and redeploying
Canadian assets. The company employed 100 people in Canada,
where it had been in business for more than 20 years.
   For its second quarter ended March 31, 1991, BJ Services
reported net income of $3.3 million, or 26 cents a share, on
revenue of $95.2 million.